President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring March 15-21, 2020 as National Poison Prevention Week in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of raising awareness about unintentional poisonings and overdoses, particularly among children. It highlights the need for individuals to take preventative measures such as safely disposing of expired medications, locking up medications, and seeking help from poison control centers in the event of an accidental poisoning. The proclamation also addresses the opioid crisis, stating that efforts are being made to combat drug addiction and decrease opioid prescription fills. The proclamation concludes by urging all Americans to take actions to protect their families from poisonous products and to raise awareness about the dangers of unintentional poisonings and drug overdoses.